 how to do it.\n\n```js\nconst Loading = () => (<div>Loading...</div>);\nconst MyPage = () => (\n  <div>\n    ....\n    <NoSSR onSSR={<Loading />}>\n      <Comments />\n    </NoSSR>\n  </div>\n);\n```\n\nThen `<Loading />` component will be rendered until `<Comments />` component is rendered to the DOM.\n","maintainers":[{"name":"arunoda","email":"arunoda.susiripala@gmail.com"}],"time":{"modified":"2022-06-26T07:24:58.474Z","created":"2016-02-19T06:29:15.262Z","1.0.0":"2016-02-19T06:29:15.262Z","1.0.1":"2016-02-19T06:32:50.975Z","1.1.0":"2016-04-09T19:41:05.926Z"},"homepage":"https://github.com/kadirahq/react-no-ssr#readme","repository":{"type":"git","url":"git+https://github.com/kadirahq/react-no-ssr.git"},"bugs":{"url":"https://github.com/kadirahq/react-no-ssr/issues"},"license":"MIT","readmeFilename":"README.md"}